{"title":"IELTS Speaking notes","uid":"0aa0465dcdf75184f7ed23532a52c943","slug":"IELTS Speaking notes","date":"2021-12-09T15:06:33.000Z","updated":"2021-12-09T15:17:24.916Z","comments":true,"path":"api/articles/IELTS Speaking notes.json","keywords":null,"cover":"https://s1.ax1x.com/2021/12/09/o4wDnf.png","content":"<h1 id=\"Some-points-of-the-IELTS-Speaking\"><a href=\"#Some-points-of-the-IELTS-Speaking\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Some points of the IELTS Speaking:\"></a>Some points of the IELTS Speaking:</h1><blockquote><span class=\"custom-blockquote-svg\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" data-reactroot=\"\">\n<path fill=\"\" d=\"M22 12C22 6.5 17.5 2 12 2C6.5 2 2 6.5 2 12C2 17.5 6.5 22 12 22C13.8 22 15.5 21.5 17 20.6L22 22L20.7 17C21.5 15.5 22 13.8 22 12Z\" undefined=\"1\"></path>\n<path fill=\"\" d=\"M15.97 11.5H16.04C17.12 11.5 18 12.38 18 13.47V13.53C18 14.62 17.12 15.5 16.03 15.5H15.96C14.88 15.5 14 14.62 14 13.53V13.46C14 12.38 14.88 11.5 15.97 11.5Z\" undefined=\"1\"></path>\n<path fill=\"\" d=\"M7.97 11.5H8.04C9.12 11.5 10 12.38 10 13.47V13.53C10 14.62 9.12 15.5 8.03 15.5H7.97C6.88 15.5 6 14.62 6 13.53V13.46C6 12.38 6.88 11.5 7.97 11.5Z\" undefined=\"1\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M17 8.5C15.23 8.97 14.07 10.84 14.01 13.27C14 13.33 14 13.4 14 13.47V13.5\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M9 8.5C7.23 8.97 6.07 10.84 6.01 13.27C6 13.33 6 13.4 6 13.47V13.5\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M15.97 11.5H16.04C17.12 11.5 18 12.38 18 13.47V13.53C18 14.62 17.12 15.5 16.03 15.5H15.96C14.88 15.5 14 14.62 14 13.53V13.46C14 12.38 14.88 11.5 15.97 11.5Z\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M7.97 11.5H8.04C9.12 11.5 10 12.38 10 13.47V13.53C10 14.62 9.12 15.5 8.03 15.5H7.97C6.88 15.5 6 14.62 6 13.53V13.46C6 12.38 6.88 11.5 7.97 11.5Z\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><p>Discourse markers</p></blockquote>\n<p>Positive: sure, definitely ,of course</p>\n<p>Negative: not at all, absolutely not, I am afraid not</p>\n<p>Personal opinions: If you ask me(C<sub>2</sub>), to me, personally</p>\n<p>Functions: to make the speech more natural and idiomatic</p>\n<h1 id=\"Basic-formula-for-part-one\"><a href=\"#Basic-formula-for-part-one\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Basic formula for part one:\"></a>Basic formula for part one:</h1><h2 id=\"Step-1\"><a href=\"#Step-1\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Step 1:\"></a>Step 1:</h2><p>Response, discourse markers + answer the question directly with full sentences</p>\n<h2 id=\"Step-2\"><a href=\"#Step-2\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Step 2:\"></a>Step 2:</h2><p>Extensions, the claw system,paralleling addition, comparison and example</p>\n<h3 id=\"Extension-1-The-claw-system\"><a href=\"#Extension-1-The-claw-system\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Extension 1: The claw system\"></a>Extension 1: The claw system</h3><p>To find out reasons behind the answer, we usually sum up reasons into 5 parts: Financial,Social, Environmental, Mental, Physical.</p>\n<p><strong>Financial:</strong> usually about money, to be more specific is living cost, job, economic growth, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Social:</strong> usually about people, to me more specific is socializing, social group, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Environmental:</strong> usually about location, atmosphere, vibe, environmental protection, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Mental:</strong> usually about emotions and feelings.</p>\n<p><strong>Physical:</strong> usually about health and body figure and physical features.</p>\n<p><strong>Besides the claw system, there is a basic structure for giving reasons:</strong></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Cause conjunction</th>\n<th>+</th>\n<th>Objective reason</th>\n<th>+</th>\n<th>Subjective feeling</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>Because</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Physical</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Mental</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>as</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Social</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>feelings</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>for</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Financial</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>emotions</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>for the reason that</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Environmental</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>owing to the fact that</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<p>PS: as can only be followed with Objective reason.</p>\n<h3 id=\"Extension-2-Paralleling-addition\"><a href=\"#Extension-2-Paralleling-addition\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Extension 2: Paralleling addition\"></a>Extension 2: Paralleling addition</h3><p>Useful connectives: also, another reason is that, besides, by the way…</p>\n<h3 id=\"Extension-3-Comparison\"><a href=\"#Extension-3-Comparison\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Extension 3: Comparison\"></a>Extension 3: Comparison</h3><p>Useful connectives: Differences: unlike, compared with, while, but, however</p>\n<p>Similarities: like, similarly, in the same way, same as</p>\n<h3 id=\"Extension-4-Example\"><a href=\"#Extension-4-Example\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Extension 4: Example\"></a>Extension 4: Example</h3><p>Useful connectives: for example, for instance, I still remember</p>\n<p>The way to give an example:</p>\n<p>Conjunction + 4WH + Subjective feeling</p>\n<p>4WH: when/ what/ where/ who</p>\n<h1 id=\"Overall-framework-for-part-1\"><a href=\"#Overall-framework-for-part-1\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Overall framework for part 1\"></a>Overall framework for part 1</h1><p>Step 1: response</p>\n<p>Learn different expressions and synonyms of “like” or “dislike”.</p>\n<p>Step 2: extensions</p>\n<p>Master different ways of extending your answers to show your willingness of communication.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://imgtu.com/i/o4wb4J\"><img src=\"https://s1.ax1x.com/2021/12/09/o4wb4J.md.jpg\" alt=\"o4wb4J.md.jpg\"></a></p>\n","feature":true,"text":"Some points of the IELTS Speaking: Discourse markers Positive: sure, definitely ,of course Negative: not at all, absolutely not, I am afraid...","link":"","photos":[],"count_time":{"symbolsCount":"2k","symbolsTime":"2 mins."},"categories":[{"name":"IELTS","slug":"IELTS","count":1,"path":"api/categories/IELTS.json"}],"tags":[{"name":"IELTS","slug":"IELTS","count":1,"path":"api/tags/IELTS.json"}],"toc":"<ol class=\"toc\"><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Some-points-of-the-IELTS-Speaking\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Some points of the IELTS Speaking:</span></a></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Basic-formula-for-part-one\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Basic formula for part one:</span></a><ol class=\"toc-child\"><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Step-1\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Step 1:</span></a></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Step-2\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Step 2:</span></a><ol class=\"toc-child\"><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Extension-1-The-claw-system\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Extension 1: The claw system</span></a></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Extension-2-Paralleling-addition\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Extension 2: Paralleling addition</span></a></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Extension-3-Comparison\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Extension 3: Comparison</span></a></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Extension-4-Example\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Extension 4: Example</span></a></li></ol></li></ol></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Overall-framework-for-part-1\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Overall framework for part 1</span></a></li></ol>